Data and R environmental variables
- Some R packages store API
tokens as R environmental variables
- R environmental variables are stored
in a .Renviron file
- By default, variables are always stored
in the .Renviron file in home folder
NOT project directory
- Check packages to know if use
.Renviron or .httr-auth


.Renviron

Package splelunking
- check function: create_token or pkg_auth
- Check the docs for a mention of .Renviron

Expirement with the package
- Use package and see if it creates
.httr-oauth file
- No .httr-oauth file? use package

Variables and shiny apps:
1. use rstudio projects
2. create .gitignore and .Renviron
NOTE! Do step 1 and 2 or else API credentials can be stolen easily
3. Create a new .Renviron variable in your
project directory

Rules .renviron file
- Use snake_Case for variables and quote values e.g.
 PACKAGE_CONSUMER_SECRET="value"